            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Titus Pompullius Lappa, son of Lucius, quinquennial duovir, military tribune elected by the people, prefect of engineers, 
                    by his will ordered a hall of auctioneers to be built and a sacred [shrine?] to be erected for Mercurius Augustus, 
                    under the supervision of his freedman Epaphra.
                </p>
